      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>James A. Brown</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>James Brown's papers consist of correspondence, diaries, conference reports, and sermons. The correspondence and diaries tell of church activities, the management of the Brown Family farm, and other family concerns. Interesting comments are made about events and personalities of the times, the depression, farming conditions, politics, and prohibition. There are conference reports for scattered dates from 1921 to 1941 and sermons delivered from 1926 to 1943. Sermons are identified as baccalaureate sermons, children's sermonettes, and general sermons.</p>
        </scopecontent>
