      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Winifred Croel Brown</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>Included in Winifred Croel Brown's papers are clippings relating to her service as an American Red Cross Gray Lady, diaries, a scrapbook, a sermon written in 1910, and a copy of her will. The diaries give an account of her daily life as the wife of a minister serving rural parishes and of her later years as a widow. The scrapbook consists mostly of poetry, but does include a few clippings relating to residents of Lyons and Ionia.</p>
        </scopecontent>
