        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Brown Family series includes papers relating to James Brown's uncle, brother, and parents. Charles Franklin Brown was James' brother. His papers include a certificate of membership in the Ancient Order of Gleaners and a copy of his will. The papers of James' parents, Joseph and Annie Brown, include marriage and citizenship certificates, an inventory of their estate, and papers relating to the administration of the estate.</p>
          <p>James Brown was the administrator of the estate of his uncle, Charles Brown. Included in the Charles Brown papers are correspondence between James and the attorney for the estate, renters of property owned by the estate, and family members who were heirs, an account book, an inventory of the estate, and legal papers relating to disposition of the property.</p>
